Prior to starting work on any HNT the Department Supervisor will provide information to all workers involved concerning the hazards involved in such tasks.



This information will include:



?    Specific chemical hazardous;

?    Protective/Safety measures the employee can take;

?    Measures BGMU has taken to lessen the hazards, including ventilation, respirators, presence of another employee and emergency procedures.



It is department policy that no employee will begin work on any Hazardous Non-routine Task without first receiving a safety briefing from the Department Supervisor or a designated Safety Officer.



CHEMICALS IN UNLABELED CONTAINERS



Storing or transporting hazardous materials in unlabeled containers is strictly prohibited; when there is the possibility that anyone other than the person who is knowledgeable of the content could come into contact with said containers.



It is the responsibility of the department supervisors to ensure proper labeling is on hazardous material containers.









INFORMING CONTRACTORS



It is the responsibility of the department supervisor to provide the contractors and their employees with the following information:



?    Hazardous chemicals to which they may be exposed while on the job site;

?    Measures the employees may take to lessen the possibility of exposure;

?    Steps BGMU has taken to lessen the risks;

